<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#0a0c0e">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Geist+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/marketing.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    @include('site-nav')

    <main>
      <nav class="shell subnav" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>Docs</span>
      </nav>

      <section class="feat-hero shell">
        <span class="kicker">Docs</span>
        <h1>Ship ghostanalytics in one line.</h1>
        <p>One first-party script under 2 KB, a tiny client call for custom events, and a read API for your numbers. No cookies, no consent banner, and no SDK to learn.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/register">Get your site ID</a>
          <a class="btn ghost" href="https://github.com/stacksjs/ghostanalytics" data-no-router>View on GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Install the script">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 class="section-title">Install the script</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">Add one tag to your site head with your site ID. It loads deferred and first-party, and starts counting page views right away, including client-side route changes in single-page apps.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="code" style="max-width: 680px">
          <div class="code-bar"><span class="chart-cap">Add to every page, once</span></div>
          <pre class="code-body"><code>&lt;script defer
  src="https://ghostanalytics.org/script.js"
  data-site="YOUR_SITE_ID"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Track custom events">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 class="section-title">Track custom events</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">Once the script has loaded it puts a ghost() function on the page. Call it on any event that matters, with optional properties, to record a conversion beside your traffic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="code" style="max-width: 680px">
          <div class="code-bar"><span class="chart-cap">On the event that matters</span></div>
          <pre class="code-body"><code>// e.g. right after a successful signup
ghost('signup', {
  plan: 'pro',
  value: 19,
})</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Read your numbers with the API">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 class="section-title">Read your numbers with the API</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">Every figure on the dashboard is available over a small read API, scoped to your site ID and an optional date range. Wire it into a status board, a scheduled report, or your own UI.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="code" style="max-width: 680px">
          <div class="code-bar"><span class="chart-cap">GET /api/sites/{siteId}/*</span></div>
          <pre class="code-body"><code>GET /api/sites/{siteId}/stats        // visitors, views, sessions
GET /api/sites/{siteId}/timeseries   // views per day
GET /api/sites/{siteId}/pages        // top pages
GET /api/sites/{siteId}/referrers    // top sources

// example
fetch('https://ghostanalytics.org/api/sites/demo/stats?from=2026-07-01&amp;to=2026-07-10')
  .then(r =&gt; r.json())
// { "views": 8, "visitors": 4, "sessions": 4 }</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Own your data">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 class="section-title">Own your data, self-host if you want</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">Every event lands in your own SingleStore database, so the numbers never leave your infrastructure and there is no third party to trust. The whole stack is open source.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="btn ghost" href="https://github.com/stacksjs/ghostanalytics" data-no-router>Read the source on GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Get started">
        <div class="cta-band">
          <h2>Start counting visitors, privately.</h2>
          <p>Add the script, watch the dashboard fill in. No cookie banner required.</p>
          <div class="cta-actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/register">Get your site ID</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/dashboard" data-no-router>See a live dashboard</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer shell">
      <div class="footer-bottom" style="border-top: none">
        <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="ghostanalytics home">
          <span class="brand-mark">g</span>
          <span class="brand-name">ghostanalytics</span>
        </a>
        <span>No cookies. No personal data. Powered by Stacks and SingleStore.</span>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
